VALUES

('watershed', 'Watershed', 'Enterprise carbon management platform for measuring, reducing, and reporting Scope 1-3 emissions',
 E'Watershed is a carbon management platform built for enterprises that need accurate, auditable measurement of their Scope 1, 2, and 3 greenhouse gas emissions and a structured program for reducing them. The platform connects directly to financial systems, energy bills, supplier data, and logistics providers to pull the raw activity data that underpins emissions calculations, then applies the GHG Protocol methodology to produce an emissions inventory that meets the standards required by CDP disclosure, TCFD reporting, and the SEC climate disclosure rules that took effect in 2025.\n\nThe Scope 3 measurement capability is where Watershed differentiates most strongly. Scope 3 - the upstream and downstream emissions in a company\'s value chain, including purchased goods, business travel, logistics, and product end-of-life - typically represents 70 to 90 percent of a company\'s total footprint but is the hardest to measure accurately. Watershed\'s supplier data collection tools, spend-based estimation models, and primary data prioritization workflows give sustainability teams a defensible Scope 3 inventory rather than rough estimates.\n\nThe platform also includes a reduction program module: target setting aligned to Science Based Targets initiative (SBTi) methodology, initiative tracking for energy efficiency and renewable procurement projects, and a carbon market integration for purchasing verified carbon credits where reduction initiatives fall short. Watershed serves mid-market and enterprise companies across technology, retail, manufacturing, and financial services. Pricing is enterprise and based on company revenue and reporting complexity.',
 'https://watershed.com', 'https://watershed.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.6, 1840, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['sustainability', 'esg', 'climate-tech'],
 ARRAY['Scope 3 supplier data collection tools produce defensible value-chain emissions inventories', 'Direct integration with financial and logistics systems pulls activity data without manual exports', 'SBTi-aligned target setting and initiative tracking in the same platform as measurement', 'Audit-ready emissions data for CDP, TCFD, and SEC climate disclosure requirements'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise pricing - not accessible for small businesses or individual sustainability practitioners', 'Scope 3 accuracy depends on supplier participation in data collection workflows', 'Full platform setup requires a structured onboarding engagement with the Watershed team', 'Carbon credit marketplace is limited relative to dedicated offset brokers'],
 ARRAY['Annual GHG inventory for CDP and regulatory climate disclosures at enterprise scale', 'Scope 3 emissions measurement across purchased goods, logistics, and supplier networks', 'Science Based Target setting and reduction initiative management for corporate climate programs'],
 NOW()),

('persefoni', 'Persefoni', 'Climate management and accounting platform for enterprise carbon footprint and TCFD reporting',
 E'Persefoni is a climate management and accounting platform designed around the disclosure and compliance needs of corporations and financial institutions. The platform applies Generally Accepted Emissions Accounting Principles (GAEAP) to produce emissions inventories that are structured like financial accounts - auditable, comparable across periods, and defensible to external assurance providers. This financial accounting framing is deliberate: Persefoni was built from the start for the world where carbon data faces the same scrutiny as financial data.\n\nThe platform covers Scope 1, 2, and 3 emissions measurement using GHG Protocol and IPCC emission factors. A dedicated financial institution module calculates financed emissions under the PCAF (Partnership for Carbon Accounting Financials) standard - the framework used by banks, asset managers, and insurance companies to measure the emissions associated with their loan and investment portfolios. For companies facing mandatory CSRD reporting in Europe or SEC climate rules in the US, Persefoni provides structured reporting outputs aligned to both frameworks.\n\nPersefoni integrates with ERP systems, expense management platforms, utility data providers, and travel management tools to automate data collection at the transactional level. The assurance module generates the documentation package that external auditors need to verify the emissions inventory - a feature set that reflects where the market is heading as carbon assurance becomes standard practice for listed companies. Persefoni is used by publicly listed companies, large private enterprises, and financial institutions across North America and Europe. Pricing is enterprise and requires a sales engagement.',
 'https://persefoni.com', 'https://persefoni.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.5, 1420, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['sustainability', 'esg', 'climate-tech'],
 ARRAY['Financial accounting framing produces audit-ready emissions data aligned to external assurance standards', 'PCAF financed emissions module covers banks, asset managers, and insurance portfolios', 'CSRD and SEC climate disclosure-aligned reporting outputs in one platform', 'ERP and expense system integrations automate data collection at transactional level'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise pricing - designed for large corporates and financial institutions, not SMBs', 'Platform depth requires a meaningful onboarding investment to configure correctly', 'Scope 3 calculation quality depends on activity data availability from suppliers and partners', 'Financial institution module requires familiarity with PCAF methodology to use effectively'],
 ARRAY['Corporate GHG inventory management for annual climate disclosure filings', 'Financed emissions calculation for banks and asset managers under PCAF standard', 'CSRD and SEC climate rule compliance reporting for listed companies operating in multiple jurisdictions'],
 NOW()),

('sweep', 'Sweep', 'Carbon management platform for net-zero strategy, reporting, and supply chain decarbonization',
 E'Sweep is a carbon management platform built around the premise that measuring emissions is only the first step - companies need an integrated tool for building a decarbonization strategy, engaging their supply chain, and reporting progress to stakeholders. The platform provides a full carbon accounting workflow: data collection from utility accounts, travel systems, and logistics providers; Scope 1, 2, and 3 calculation using GHG Protocol methodology; and a strategy module for building time-bound reduction roadmaps aligned to net-zero targets.\n\nThe supply chain engagement module is a core differentiator. Sweep allows companies to invite their suppliers to share emissions data directly within the platform, converting Scope 3 category 1 (purchased goods and services) from an estimated figure to primary-data-backed measurement. For companies where supply chain emissions dominate the total footprint, this supplier engagement capability is central to a credible decarbonization program. Sweep provides a lightweight supplier onboarding experience so even small vendors can participate without deploying a full sustainability platform themselves.\n\nSweep\'s reporting module generates outputs for CDP questionnaires, GRI standards, TCFD, and CSRD. The platform also includes an offset procurement integration for bridging the gap between reduction targets and current performance while longer-term initiatives deliver results. Sweep is used by companies across financial services, retail, manufacturing, and professional services in Europe and North America. The company is headquartered in Paris, making it particularly well-positioned for European companies navigating CSRD requirements. Pricing scales with revenue and reporting complexity.',
 'https://sweep.net', 'https://sweep.net',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.4, 1080, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['sustainability', 'esg', 'climate-tech'],
 ARRAY['Supply chain engagement module enables primary Scope 3 data collection from suppliers', 'Net-zero strategy module builds time-bound decarbonization roadmaps from the measured baseline', 'CDP, GRI, TCFD, and CSRD reporting outputs in a single platform', 'Paris-based with strong CSRD expertise for European regulatory requirements'],
 ARRAY['Supply chain Scope 3 accuracy depends on supplier participation rates in data collection', 'Platform is deeper on strategy and reporting than on operational emissions reduction tracking', 'Enterprise pricing with no self-serve option for smaller organizations', 'Offset marketplace is basic compared to dedicated carbon credit brokers'],
 ARRAY['Annual carbon accounting and CDP disclosure for mid-market and enterprise companies', 'Scope 3 supplier engagement programs to replace spend-based estimates with primary data', 'CSRD-aligned sustainability reporting for European companies and multinationals'],
 NOW()),

('normative', 'Normative', 'Carbon accounting engine that calculates spend-based emissions for any company automatically',
 E'Normative is a carbon accounting platform built around automated spend-based emissions calculation. The platform connects to accounting systems, ERP data, and financial records, then applies emission factors from Normative\'s proprietary database - covering over 20 million supply chain emission factors across 163 countries - to convert financial spend data into a Scope 1, 2, and 3 emissions inventory. The result is a complete carbon footprint from existing financial data without manual collection from every supplier.\n\nThe spend-based approach is deliberately positioned as the entry point for companies that need a credible emissions baseline quickly. Rather than spending 12 months collecting primary data from suppliers before publishing a first inventory, Normative produces a defensible estimate from financial data within days of connecting accounting systems. The platform then provides tools to improve accuracy progressively - replacing spend-based estimates with primary data for the highest-impact Scope 3 categories as supplier engagement matures.\n\nNormative\'s emission factor database is one of the largest in the industry and is updated quarterly to reflect changes in grid electricity factors, industry benchmarks, and IPCC guidance. The platform supports disclosure to CDP, GRI, TCFD, and the CSRD. A team of carbon accounting experts is available to guide customers through methodology choices and disclosure requirements. Normative is used by mid-market companies across Europe and North America that need to move quickly from no measurement to disclosed inventory. Pricing is subscription-based, with tiers designed for companies from 50 to several thousand employees.',
 'https://normative.io', 'https://normative.io',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.3, 960, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['sustainability', 'esg', 'climate-tech'],
 ARRAY['Spend-based calculation from accounting data produces a complete Scope 3 inventory without supplier collection', 'Over 20 million supply chain emission factors across 163 countries in the database', 'Inventory produced in days from financial data - faster to first disclosure than primary data approaches', 'Quarterly database updates keep emission factors current with IPCC and grid electricity changes'],
 ARRAY['Spend-based estimates are less accurate than primary supplier data for Scope 3 categories 1 and 2', 'Platform depth on reduction strategy and initiative tracking is lighter than Watershed or Sweep', 'European company - less North American enterprise market penetration than US-founded competitors', 'Requires clean, categorized accounting data for most accurate output'],
 ARRAY['First-year carbon inventory for companies with no prior emissions measurement program', 'Scope 3 estimation from financial spend data for annual CDP and CSRD disclosure', 'Carbon accounting for mid-market companies that cannot afford enterprise platform pricing'],
 NOW()),

('plan-a', 'Plan A', 'Sustainability platform for decarbonization management, ESG reporting, and net-zero programs',
 E'Plan A is a sustainability management platform providing carbon accounting, ESG reporting, and decarbonization strategy tools to mid-market and enterprise companies. The platform covers Scope 1, 2, and 3 emissions measurement using GHG Protocol methodology, ESG data management across environmental, social, and governance metrics, and reporting frameworks including GRI, SASB, TCFD, CDP, and CSRD. This breadth positions Plan A as an all-in-one sustainability platform rather than a carbon-only tool.\n\nThe decarbonization module allows sustainability managers to build reduction roadmaps with initiative tracking, science-based target alignment, and scenario modeling that projects how different combinations of initiatives affect the emissions trajectory over time. For sustainability teams that need to present a credible net-zero plan to board and investor audiences, the scenario modeling feature is particularly useful for building the narrative from current baseline to 2030 and 2050 targets.\n\nPlan A is headquartered in Berlin and serves companies primarily in Germany, the UK, and across Europe, where CSRD compliance is driving urgent demand for structured sustainability management. The platform integrates with SAP, Microsoft Dynamics, and other ERP systems for automated data collection. A marketplace of climate consultants and assurance providers is accessible within the platform for companies that need external support alongside the software. Pricing is modular and scales by the number of users, reporting frameworks required, and data integration complexity.',
 'https://plan-a.earth', 'https://plan-a.earth',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.3, 1120, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['sustainability', 'esg', 'climate-tech'],
 ARRAY['Full ESG coverage across environmental, social, and governance metrics beyond carbon-only', 'Decarbonization scenario modeling helps sustainability teams build credible net-zero roadmaps', 'Strong CSRD coverage with Berlin-based European regulatory expertise', 'Marketplace of climate consultants and assurance providers integrated within the platform'],
 ARRAY['European focus means less depth for companies primarily subject to US regulatory requirements', 'Breadth of ESG coverage means less depth in any single area versus specialist carbon platforms', 'Platform setup for all frameworks and integrations requires a structured implementation engagement', 'Smaller market presence than Watershed or Persefoni in North America'],
 ARRAY['CSRD sustainability reporting for European companies across all ESG pillars', 'Decarbonization roadmap and target management for corporate net-zero programs', 'Integrated ESG data management for companies reporting to multiple frameworks simultaneously'],
 NOW()),

('climatiq', 'Climatiq', 'Carbon emission factor API for developers building sustainability features into any application',
 E'Climatiq is an emission factor API that enables developers and product teams to add accurate carbon calculation to any application, workflow, or data pipeline without building and maintaining an emission factor database internally. The API provides access to a curated, regularly-updated database of emission factors from IPCC, IEA, EPA, DEFRA, and other authoritative sources, covering electricity generation by grid and hour, freight and logistics by mode and distance, air travel by route and class, materials and manufacturing processes, and hundreds of other activity categories.\n\nThe core use case is embedding emissions calculation into products and services: a logistics platform calculating the carbon footprint of each shipment at the booking step, an expense management tool showing the emissions of each business trip, a procurement system flagging the carbon intensity of supplier products, or a fintech app showing users the carbon footprint of their purchases. Climatiq handles the emission factor management and methodology updates so developers can focus on building the feature rather than maintaining the data.\n\nClimatiq provides a REST API with SDKs for Python, JavaScript, and other languages. An Estimates endpoint handles common calculation patterns without the developer needing to know the underlying methodology details. The database covers over 50,000 emission factors across 150+ countries. A dashboard provides usage monitoring and factor browsing. The platform also serves sustainability teams at non-developer organizations through a no-code calculation interface. Free tier covers 100 API calls per month; paid plans start at $99/month for higher volumes and commercial usage.',
 'https://climatiq.io', 'https://climatiq.io',
 'freemium', true, 99, 4.4, 780, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['climate-tech', 'sustainability', 'developer-tools'],
 ARRAY['API-first design lets developers embed carbon calculation in any product without building emission factor databases', 'Over 50,000 emission factors from authoritative sources updated regularly', 'Coverage spans electricity, freight, travel, materials, and manufacturing processes globally', 'Free tier available for prototyping and low-volume use cases'],
 ARRAY['Developer-focused product - non-technical sustainability teams need the no-code interface or a developer', 'Emission factor accuracy still has inherent uncertainty in some categories - not a substitute for primary data', 'Advanced use cases require understanding of GHG Protocol methodology to use correctly', 'Support depth is lighter than enterprise sustainability platforms'],
 ARRAY['Embedding real-time carbon footprint calculation in logistics, travel, or e-commerce platforms', 'Building sustainability reporting features into ERP, finance, or procurement software products', 'Prototyping carbon calculation features for startups and product teams without in-house emissions expertise'],
 NOW()),

('ibm-envizi', 'IBM Envizi', 'ESG data management platform for enterprise sustainability performance reporting and analytics',
 E'IBM Envizi is an enterprise ESG data management platform that consolidates energy, emissions, water, waste, and social data from across large organizations into a single system of record for sustainability performance reporting and analytics. The platform was acquired by IBM in 2022 and has since been integrated into the IBM Sustainability software portfolio, positioned as the data foundation layer for large corporations managing complex sustainability reporting across hundreds or thousands of sites globally.\n\nEnvizi\'s core strength is data management at scale: the platform handles automated data collection from utility providers via EDI feeds, meter data, and manual entry workflows, normalizes it across different currencies, units, and reporting periods, and produces location-based and market-based Scope 2 emissions calculations alongside Scope 1 and Scope 3 estimates. Interval data analysis identifies energy efficiency opportunities at the facility level from granular consumption patterns. The reporting module produces outputs for CDP, GRI, SASB, TCFD, and regulatory frameworks including CSRD and Australia\'s NGER.\n\nFor organizations with a large real estate footprint - retailers, banks with branch networks, manufacturers with multiple facilities, or hospitality groups with hundreds of properties - Envizi\'s ability to aggregate and normalize data across disparate sites is the primary value driver. The platform integrates with SAP, Salesforce, and other enterprise systems through IBM\'s integration layer. IBM Envizi is positioned at the large enterprise end of the market. Pricing is enterprise and requires engagement with IBM or an IBM Business Partner.',
 'https://ibm.com/products/envizi', 'https://ibm.com/products/envizi',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.2, 1340, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['sustainability', 'esg', 'enterprise'],
 ARRAY['Handles ESG data management at scale across hundreds or thousands of sites globally', 'Automated utility data ingestion via EDI feeds reduces manual data collection burden', 'Interval data analysis identifies facility-level energy efficiency opportunities', 'CDP, GRI, TCFD, CSRD, and NGER reporting outputs from a single data platform'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise-only pricing through IBM direct sales or IBM Business Partners', 'Platform complexity scales with organizational complexity - significant implementation effort for large deployments', 'Less agile product development cadence than pure-play sustainability software startups', 'Integration with non-IBM systems adds implementation complexity and cost'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise energy and emissions data management across large real estate and manufacturing footprints', 'Annual CDP, GRI, and regulatory sustainability disclosure for multinational corporations', 'Facility-level energy efficiency analytics for retailers, banks, and hospitality groups with large property portfolios'],
 NOW()),

('emitwise', 'Emitwise', 'AI-powered carbon management platform for manufacturing companies tracking Scope 1-3 emissions',
 E'Emitwise is a carbon management platform built specifically for manufacturing companies, addressing the particular challenge that manufacturers face: their emissions profile is dominated by Scope 1 (direct combustion and process emissions from facilities) and Scope 3 upstream (purchased raw materials and components), both of which require more granular data and more complex calculation methodologies than the spend-based approaches that work adequately for service-sector companies.\n\nThe platform uses AI to automate data extraction from the documents, invoices, and system exports that manufacturing companies already have - energy bills, production records, material purchase orders, logistics records - and converts them into a structured emissions dataset without manual re-entry. Machine learning models classify documents, extract relevant quantities, and map them to the correct emission factor categories, dramatically reducing the data preparation time that makes carbon accounting painful for operations teams without dedicated sustainability staff.\n\nEmitwise covers Scope 1, 2, and 3 calculation, target setting, and reporting for CDP, TCFD, and CSRD. The platform includes a supplier engagement module for collecting primary Scope 3 data from key suppliers. For manufacturers that have avoided carbon accounting because of the perceived data complexity, Emitwise\'s AI-powered data ingestion addresses the main practical barrier. The company is backed by notable climate tech investors and has particular strength in European manufacturing. Pricing is subscription-based and scales with the number of facilities and data sources.',
 'https://emitwise.com', 'https://emitwise.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.3, 840, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['sustainability', 'manufacturing', 'climate-tech'],
 ARRAY['AI document extraction automates data ingestion from invoices, energy bills, and production records', 'Manufacturing-specific - handles Scope 1 process emissions and complex upstream Scope 3 categories', 'Reduces data preparation time for operations teams without dedicated sustainability staff', 'Supplier engagement module for primary Scope 3 data collection from key material suppliers'],
 ARRAY['Smaller vendor - less brand recognition than Watershed or Persefoni in the enterprise market', 'AI extraction accuracy on unusual document formats may require manual review and correction', 'Primarily European manufacturing focus - less depth for North American regulatory frameworks', 'Platform is narrower than full ESG platforms - focused on carbon rather than all sustainability metrics'],
 ARRAY['Carbon accounting automation for manufacturers with complex Scope 1 and Scope 3 profiles', 'CDP and CSRD climate disclosure for European manufacturing companies', 'Supplier carbon data collection for manufacturers decarbonizing their upstream supply chains'],
 NOW()),

('greenly', 'Greenly', 'Carbon footprint platform for SMBs with accounting integration and employee engagement tools',
 E'Greenly is a carbon footprint platform designed for small and mid-size businesses that want to measure their emissions, report to customers and partners, and engage employees in sustainability - without the cost and complexity of enterprise-grade carbon management platforms. The platform connects to accounting software (QuickBooks, Xero, Sage) and bank transactions to extract spend data, applies emission factors to produce a Scope 1, 2, and 3 carbon inventory, and presents results in an accessible dashboard that non-specialist managers can interpret.\n\nThe SMB positioning is deliberate and consistent throughout the product. Onboarding is designed to produce a first emissions estimate within a working day from connected financial data. The reporting module generates a carbon footprint report formatted for sharing with enterprise customers that are starting to ask suppliers about their carbon footprint as part of procurement qualification. This bottom-up pressure from large corporate customers is driving SMB adoption of carbon accounting, and Greenly is well-positioned to serve companies responding to that demand.\n\nAn employee engagement module allows companies to communicate their climate program internally and track individual carbon reduction actions. A marketplace connects customers with climate experts and offset providers. Greenly is headquartered in Paris and serves companies across Europe and North America. The platform has strong NPS scores among SMB customers who value accessibility and speed to first report. Pricing starts at around $500 per year for small companies, scaling with company size and reporting complexity.',
 'https://greenly.earth', 'https://greenly.earth',
 'paid', false, 500, 4.4, 2100, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['sustainability', 'esg', 'climate-tech'],
 ARRAY['SMB-accessible pricing starting under $1,000 per year for small companies', 'Accounting software integration produces first inventory from existing financial data in one day', 'Supplier-ready carbon reports for SMBs responding to enterprise customer procurement requirements', 'Employee engagement module communicates climate program internally alongside the measurement tools'],
 ARRAY['Spend-based calculation is less accurate than primary data collection for Scope 3 materiality', 'Less depth on decarbonization strategy and SBTi alignment than enterprise-focused platforms', 'Customer support and advisory depth is lighter than the hands-on service of enterprise platforms', 'Limited to carbon-focused metrics - not a full ESG platform for companies needing broader sustainability reporting'],
 ARRAY['First carbon footprint measurement for SMBs responding to customer or investor carbon disclosure requests', 'Annual carbon inventory for CDP disclosure at small company scale', 'Employee carbon engagement programs for companies building an internal sustainability culture'],
