('cogo', 'CoGo', 'Carbon footprint API for banks and fintechs connecting spending to personal and business emissions',
 E'CoGo is a carbon footprint platform that embeds carbon impact data into banking and fintech products, enabling banks, neobanks, and financial apps to show customers the carbon footprint of their spending transactions in real time. The platform provides an API and white-label module that financial services companies integrate into their mobile apps and online banking portals, powered by CoGo\'s spend-based emission factor database and transaction classification engine.\n\nThe B2B2C model positions CoGo differently from other carbon platforms: rather than selling directly to companies measuring their own footprint, CoGo partners with financial institutions to deliver carbon awareness to retail and business customers through the banking interface they already use daily. For banks navigating increasing regulatory pressure to demonstrate climate relevance and engagement with customers on sustainability, CoGo provides a ready-made product integration rather than a custom build.\n\nCoGo also offers a direct carbon management product for business banking customers - allowing small business owners to see the carbon footprint of their business spending, set reduction targets, and access offset purchasing integrated within their banking app. The company operates primarily in the UK and New Zealand, where partnerships with major banks including NatWest, ASB Bank, and Westpac have established the transaction footprinting model in mainstream banking. The API is expanding to serve European and North American financial institutions. Pricing is B2B via API licensing to financial institutions; consumer-facing features are white-labeled by the bank partner.',
 'https://cogo.co', 'https://cogo.co',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.1, 680, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['climate-tech', 'sustainability', 'fintech'],
 ARRAY['Embeds carbon footprint data into banking apps without banks building the data infrastructure themselves', 'Transaction classification engine maps financial spend to emission categories at scale', 'Established banking partnerships in UK and New Zealand validate the B2B2C model', 'Business banking module helps SMBs measure carbon footprint through their existing bank relationship'],
 ARRAY['B2B API model - end customers access CoGo through their bank, not directly', 'UK and NZ market focus means limited coverage for banks primarily in other regions', 'Spend-based transaction footprinting has inherent estimation uncertainty at the individual transaction level', 'Smaller vendor with limited enterprise support infrastructure compared to ESG platform leaders'],
 ARRAY['Bank mobile app carbon footprint feature for retail and SMB customers using transaction data', 'White-label sustainability engagement product for banks responding to climate-related regulatory expectations', 'Small business carbon accounting delivered through business banking channels without separate platform adoption'],
 NOW())

